## Background and Motivation

It's simple to define a custom action filter via inheriting the `ActionFilterAttribute`, maybe we could add `AuthorizationFilterAttribute` likes `ActionFilterAttribute` to simplify the custom authorization filter

## Proposed API

```diff
namespace Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Filters;

+ [AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Class | AttributeTargets.Method, AllowMultiple = true, Inherited = true)]
+ public abstract class ActionFilterAttribute : Attribute, IAuthorizationFilter, IAsyncAuthorizationFilter
+ {
+     public virtual void OnAuthorization(AuthorizationFilterContext context) {}
+     public virtual Task OnAuthorizationAsync(AuthorizationFilterContext context)
+     {
+         ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(context);
+         OnAuthorization(context);
+         return Task.CompletedTask;
+      }
+ }

```

## Usage Examples

``` C#
public class MyAuthorizationFilterAttribute: AuthorizationFilterAttribute
{
    public override void OnAuthorization(AuthorizationFilterContext context) 
    {
        // ...
    }
}
```

Use on controller or action  as attribute

``` c#
public class ValuesController: ControllerBase
{
    [MyAuthorizationFilter]
    public IActionResult Index(){}
}
```

## Risks

Since it would be a new type, think it's no risk from what I can see

